<paragraph pageNumber="90">
The distinction of 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:1AE6B6D0-01A8-43E7-9505-E6855D1FC99A" class="Actinopterygii" family="Ariidae" genus="Plicofollis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Plicofollis Kailola 2004:141" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="90" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Plicofollis</taxonomicName>
is also supported by four unique characters within the 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Ariidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="90" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Ariidae</taxonomicName>
, not present in 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Ariidae" genus="Plicofollis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="90" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platystomus">P. platystomus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Ariidae" genus="Plicofollis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="90" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuispinis">Plicofollis tenuispinis</taxonomicName>
: lateral ethmoid expanded (fig. 81); vomer oval shaped (fig. 83); lateral processes of vomer very short (fig. 83); uncinate process of third pharyngobranchial longer and wider than mesial portion of epibranchial (fig. 80).
</paragraph>
